.TH "geni_se_tx_dma_prep" 9 "geni_se_tx_dma_prep" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
geni_se_tx_dma_prep \- Prepare the serial engine for TX DMA transfer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" geni_se_tx_dma_prep
.BI "(struct geni_se *se "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *iova "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "se" 12
Pointer to the concerned serial engine.
.IP "buf" 12
Pointer to the TX buffer.
.IP "len" 12
Length of the TX buffer.
.IP "iova" 12
Pointer to store the mapped DMA address.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to prepare the buffers for DMA TX.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, standard Linux error codes on failure.
